IBADAN – Senator Iyiola Omisore, a former deputy governor of Osun State, has commiserated with the Chairman of the Senate Committee on Local Content Senator Teslim Folarin over the death of his late wife, Barrister Angela Folarin. Senator Omisore in the condolence message personally signed by him on Saturday described the death of Barrister Angela Folarin on Friday in the United Kingdom as sad and shocking. The former deputy governor stressed that the late Barrister Angela Folarin will be greatly missed by her immediate family, friends and associates. Ashafa Commiserates With Sanwo-Olu Over… Soludo Commiserates With Val On Father’s Death “On behalf of myself and my family, I condole Senator Teslim Kolawole Folarin on the death of his amiable wife, Barrister Angela Folarin. The death is sad, shocking and unbelievable.” Senator Omisore stressed that the news of the death of Barrister Angela Folarin came to him as a rude shock, adding, that the vacuum created by her death in the Folarin family will be difficult to fill. While consoling Senator Teslim Folarin, the entire Folarin family over the death of Barrister Angela Folarin, Senator Omisore prayed that God will give Senator Folarin and the entire family the fortitude to bear the loss.